@startuml URL Processing Logic Flow
!theme plain
title DaySave URL Processing Logic Flow

actor User as U
participant "Backend Route" as BR
participant "AutomationOrchestrator" as AO
participant "UrlProcessor" as UP
participant "WebsiteProcessor" as WP
participant "BackwardCompatibilityService" as BCS
participant "MultimediaAnalyzer" as MA
database "Database" as DB

note over U, DB
  Current URL Processing Architecture
  Handles both multimedia URLs and general websites
end note

U -> BR: Submit URL for processing
activate BR

BR -> AO: processUrl(url, options)
activate AO

note right of AO
  AutomationOrchestrator is the central coordinator
  Uses singleton pattern for system-wide coordination
end note

AO -> UP: isMultimediaUrl(url)
activate UP
UP -> UP: Check against multimedia patterns
note right of UP
  Patterns include:
  - YouTube (youtube.com, youtu.be)
  - Instagram, TikTok, Facebook
  - Vimeo, Dailymotion, Twitch
  - SoundCloud, Spotify
  - Direct media files (.mp4, .mp3, etc.)
end note
UP --> AO: boolean result
deactivate UP

AO -> UP: isWebsiteUrl(url)
activate UP
UP -> UP: Check URL structure
note right of UP
  Website URL criteria:
  - HTTP/HTTPS protocol
  - NOT a multimedia platform
  - NOT a direct media file
  - General website content
end note
UP --> AO: boolean result
deactivate UP

alt Neither multimedia nor website
  AO -> AO: throw Error("URL not supported")
  AO --> BR: Error response
  BR --> U: Error message
else Valid URL detected
  AO -> AO: Create job record with unique ID
  
  alt Website URL detected
    note over AO, WP
      Website Processing Path
      For general business websites, blogs, etc.
    end note
    
    AO -> WP: process(userId, url, options)
    activate WP
    
    WP -> WP: fetchWebsiteContent(url)
    note right of WP
      HTTP fetch with:
      - User-Agent headers
      - Redirect following
      - Size limits (5MB)
      - Timeout (30s)
    end note
    
    WP -> WP: extractWebsiteData($, url)
    note right of WP
      Extract:
      - Title, description, keywords
      - Text content (max 50k chars)
      - Headings (h1-h6)
      - Links and social media links
    end note
    
    WP -> WP: detectEmbeddedMedia($, url)
    note right of WP
      Detect:
      - Images (max 10)
      - Embedded videos (YouTube, Vimeo, etc.)
      - Audio elements
    end note
    
    WP -> WP: analyzeContent(websiteData)
    note right of WP
      Basic analysis:
      - Word count, reading time
      - Business type detection
      - Topic extraction
    end note
    
    alt Google AI available
      WP -> WP: generateAIInsights(websiteData)
      note right of WP
        AI-powered:
        - Content summarization
        - Tag generation
        - Category classification
        - Title improvement
      end note
    end
    
    WP --> AO: Website processing result
    deactivate WP
    
    AO -> AO: Convert to standard format
    note right of AO
      Standardize output:
      - Map website result to multimedia format
      - Include metadata, summary, tags
      - Set platform as 'website'
    end note
    
  else Multimedia URL detected
    note over AO, UP
      Multimedia Processing Path
      For YouTube, social media, streaming platforms
    end note
    
    AO -> UP: analyzeUrlContent(url, options)
    activate UP
    
    UP -> UP: extractUrlMetadata(url)
    note right of UP
      Platform detection:
      - Extract video IDs
      - Generate thumbnails URLs
      - Set platform-specific metadata
    end note
    
    UP -> UP: detectPlatform(url)
    note right of UP
      Platform-specific handling:
      - YouTube: video ID extraction
      - Instagram: post detection
      - TikTok: content analysis
      - etc.
    end note
    
    alt YouTube URL
      UP -> UP: getYouTubeTranscription(url)
      note right of UP
        YouTube Processing:
        1. Extract video ID
        2. Try yt-dlp caption extraction
        3. Fallback to audio download
        4. Convert VTT to plain text
      end note
      
      UP -> UP: extractYouTubeTranscriptionWithYtDlp(url)
      note right of UP
        yt-dlp command:
        - Extract auto-generated captions
        - Extract manual captions
        - Output VTT format
        - Convert to text
      end note
      
      alt Transcription successful
        UP -> UP: generateSummary(transcription)
        UP -> UP: analyzeSentiment(transcription)
        UP -> UP: estimateSpeakerCount(transcription)
      end
    end
    
    UP -> UP: generateTags(results)
    UP -> UP: generateCategory(results)
    UP -> UP: generateTitle(results)
    
    UP --> AO: Multimedia analysis result
    deactivate UP
  end
  
  AO -> AO: Store job results
  AO -> AO: Update metrics
  AO -> AO: Clean up active job
  
  AO --> BR: Complete processing result
  deactivate AO
  
  BR -> DB: Store analysis results
  activate DB
  note right of DB
    Store in appropriate tables:
    - Content metadata
    - Analysis results
    - Transcriptions
    - Tags and categories
  end note
  DB --> BR: Storage confirmation
  deactivate DB
  
  BR --> U: Processing complete with results
end

deactivate BR

note over AO, UP
  **Key Processing Features:**
  
  **URL Validation:**
  - Multimedia pattern matching
  - Website structure validation
  - Protocol verification
  
  **Multimedia Support:**
  - YouTube transcription via yt-dlp
  - Social media content detection
  - Direct media file support
  
  **Website Analysis:**
  - Content scraping and extraction
  - AI-powered summarization
  - Business type detection
  
  **Error Handling:**
  - Graceful fallbacks
  - Timeout management
  - Invalid URL rejection
end note

note over BCS, MA
  **Backward Compatibility:**
  The system maintains compatibility with
  legacy MultimediaAnalyzer through
  BackwardCompatibilityService
end note

@enduml
